Race.SpecificTitle: Constable -- Justice of the Peace Ward 5
Fire District Number Four -- 10.30 Mills - BOC - 10 Yrs.
Race.SummaryText:
Fire District Number Four Proposition 
(Millage Continuation)
Race.FullText: Shall Caddo Parish Fire District Number Four, State of Louisiana (the "District"), continue to levy and collect a special tax not to exceed ten and thirty-hundredths (10.30) mills on all the property subject to taxation in the District (an estimated $599,000 reasonably expected at this time to be collected from the levy of the tax for an entire year), for a period of ten (10) years, beginning with the year 2015 and ending with the year 2024, for the purpose of maintaining and operating the District's fire protection facilities for purchasing fire trucks and other fire fighting equipment and paying the cost of obtaining water for fire protection purposes, including charges for fire hydrant rentals and service, said millage to represent a thirty hundredths of a mill (.30) increase over the 10 mills tax authorized to be levied through the year 2014 pursuant to an election held on November 2, 2004?
